Philippine Stocks: Cebu Air, Semirara Mining, SM Investments

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-28T02:23:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/philippine-stocks-cebu-air-semirara-mining-sm-investments.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:22 a.m. in Manila  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 7.68, or 0.2
percent, to 4,329.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  , the largest Philippine budget
carrier, advanced 1.4 percent to 79.10 pesos, set for its
sharpest gain since April 20. The airline said it flew 28
percent more passengers in the first quarter for its routes in
North Asia.  Semirara Mining Corp. (SCC)  , the nation’s biggest coal
producer, advanced 3.1 percent to 224 pesos, heading for the
sharpest gain since March 18. The company said it will pay 10
pesos a share in dividend, its highest payout based on data
going back to 2004.  SM Investments Corp. (SM)  , holding company of Philippine
billionaire Henry Sy, climbed 2.8 percent to 575.5 pesos,
heading for the highest close since Nov. 9. The company’s board
approved a 9.04 peso per share dividend payable on or before
June 22, Vice Chairman  Henry Sy  Jr. said. The payout is the
company’s highest based on data going back to 2006.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
